  "texts": [
    "Natural gradient methods, conversely, adjust the update direction based on the intrinsic geometry of the policy parameter space, promoting more effective learning steps.",
    "This nuanced understanding of the parameter space's geometry enhances convergence speed and algorithmic performance, showcasing the sophisticated nature of actor-critic methods in tackling RL challenges.A survey by Grondman et al. [32] on actor-critic methods underscores their significance in the RL domain.",
    "By offering an analysis of both standard and natural policy gradients, the survey highlights the evolution and effectiveness of these methods across various applications, including robotics and power control.",
    "Robotic ConceptsIn this study, we explore a real-world robotic application as one of our case studies.",
    "This section is specifically crafted to explain the concepts essential for understanding the functionality and purpose of the application."
  ]
}